// Semantic direction:
// native_list is a dynamic array: a header with len, cap, and a pointer to the data region.
// list_data_n is a contiguous array of native_value elements in heap memory.
// list_grow_n doubles list_cap_n and reallocates; growth_factor is typically 2.
// list_push_n appends one value; if list_len_n == list_cap_n, list_grow_n is called first.
// list_remove_n shifts remaining elements left; O(n) for interior removal.
// list_slice_n returns a new list containing the specified range without copying data (shared view).
// list_iter_n allows iterating over elements without index arithmetic in generated code.
// native_map is an open-addressed hash table with robin_hood_probe for low-overhead probing.
// map_buckets is a flat array of (hash, key, value) triples.
// robin_hood_probe displaces entries with shorter probe_distance to keep average probes low.
// backward_shift_delete removes an entry and shifts neighbors to close the gap (no tombstones).
// max_load_factor is 0.75; map_grow_n doubles cap and rehashes when exceeded.
// hash_int_n uses a mixing function to spread integer keys uniformly.
// hash_str_n processes the string bytes with a fast hash (e.g. FNV-1a or wyhash).
// hash_mix_n finalizes a partial hash to improve bit distribution.
// legg_til_n and fjern_n are the native implementations of the list builtins.
// sorter_n sorts the list in-place using an adaptive introsort.
// nøkler_n allocates a new list and copies all map keys into it.

// Primitive flow:
// list_push: if len == cap: list_grow (realloc data to 2*cap) -> data[len] = value -> len++
// list_get: bounds_check(idx, len) -> return data[idx]
// map_set: hash = hash_fn(key) -> probe from hash % cap:
//   empty slot: insert (hash, key, value) -> len++; if len/cap > max_load: map_grow
//   matching key: update value
//   displacement: robin_hood swap if probe_distance(slot) > distance(entry)
// map_get: hash = hash_fn(key) -> probe until empty or matching key -> return value or null
// map_grow: new_cap = 2*cap -> alloc new_buckets -> rehash all entries -> free old

// This defines native list and map data structures: dynamic arrays, robin hood
// hashing, grow policies, and native builtin implementations.
